  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0db8 \u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0dba\u0dda \u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dcf \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda \u0da2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A wire cutting racket at the construction stoppages of the Central Expressway",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the report, in some areas of the Kadavata-Mirigama section of the Central Expressway, there is a smuggling operation in which wire parts used for concrete are cut and sold for iron.",
        "The project workers point out that there is a situation where the wire sections used outside are secretly cut by connecting the concrete sections during the preparation of the road and thus, due to the cutting of the wire, additional expenses will have to be incurred during the reset.",
        "A group of project workers said that in the areas of Gampaha and Mirigama where the construction work has stopped, the wires are being cut and sold into iron and thus people's money will have to be spent in re-construction based on cutting the wires."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "the Central Expressway",
          "label": "LOC"
        }
